40:35.020 --> 40:37.340
and that we get to have this together

40:37.340 --> 40:39.540
without somebody
constantly interrupting us.

40:40.660 --> 40:41.963
That's probably too much.

40:42.920 --> 40:44.280
I feel like we connect, you know?

40:44.280 --> 40:47.238
Like you really see me...

40:47.238 --> 40:49.281
in a way that other people don't.

40:49.281 --> 40:51.700
(disturbing music)

40:51.700 --> 40:52.533
Holly...

40:53.370 --> 40:56.544
would you like to stay here with me?

40:56.544 --> 40:57.620
(phone beeps)

40:57.620 --> 40:58.453
One sec.

41:24.490 --> 41:25.393
Just a work thing.

41:27.115 --> 41:28.638
What were you saying?

41:28.638 --> 41:31.904
(soft orchestral music)

41:31.904 --> 41:32.737
Right.

41:39.317 --> 41:41.984
(ominous music)

41:48.120 --> 41:48.953
- Okay, check it out.

41:48.953 --> 41:52.380
These are all photos from
Heather Beech's social accounts.

41:52.380 --> 41:53.820
What do you see?

41:53.820 --> 41:56.120
- A bar mitzvah.

41:56.120 --> 41:58.063
- Cute lady and her nephew?

41:59.227 --> 42:01.440
- What about this one? Look close.

42:01.440 --> 42:02.713
- Football and failure.

42:03.850 --> 42:05.010
- I like her top.

42:05.010 --> 42:07.210
- Jesus, Sherlock! The necklace!

42:07.210 --> 42:10.330
Look, she's wearing a necklace
in all of these photos.

42:10.330 --> 42:13.623
Birthdays, New Year's, date night.

42:14.490 --> 42:16.523
They never found that necklace.

42:17.500 --> 42:19.210
- I don't wanna blow your mind right now,

42:19.210 --> 42:21.830
but people do take off their jewelry.

42:21.830 --> 42:24.680
- Yeah, yeah, so what?

42:24.680 --> 42:26.547
- I talked to her family last night.

42:26.547 --> 42:27.960
- You...

42:27.960 --> 42:29.456
You talked to her family?

42:29.456 --> 42:30.289
That's-

42:30.289 --> 42:31.330
- That's not the point.

42:31.330 --> 42:34.040
This isn't just some normal necklace.

42:34.040 --> 42:36.940
Her mother gave it to her before she died.

42:36.940 --> 42:38.910
Why would she stop wearing this necklace

42:38.910 --> 42:40.890
on the night she was murdered?

42:40.890 --> 42:42.730
- I mean, like, I know
you love your bracelet,

42:42.730 --> 42:45.470
but not everybody wears jewelry every day.

42:45.470 --> 42:47.000
- You said it yourself.

42:47.000 --> 42:49.750
He likes something that she's
wearing, and he wants it.

42:50.650 --> 42:52.590
It could be jewelry.

42:52.590 --> 42:54.950
He's taking these things as a trophy.

42:54.950 --> 42:56.240
- What about these stories?

42:56.240 --> 42:58.460
Have you read all of these
or just the ones with photos?

42:58.460 --> 42:59.940
- Okay, assuming that the police

42:59.940 --> 43:02.150
already have all of this information,

43:02.150 --> 43:03.520
what does your discovery mean

43:03.520 --> 43:05.510
for what we're doing right now?

43:05.510 --> 43:06.840
- I was thinking...

43:06.840 --> 43:09.230
maybe we try to tackle this
from a different angle.

43:09.230 --> 43:10.290
- Okay.

43:10.290 --> 43:12.993
- Instead of the dark and
brooding silent killer,

43:14.140 --> 43:15.973
what if we kick it up a notch?

43:16.880 --> 43:19.483
Maybe he's charismatic, a little flashy.

43:20.380 --> 43:22.000
Woos women?

43:22.000 --> 43:24.053
Takes the jury as trophies.

43:25.160 --> 43:27.393
- So like if Batman were a criminal.

43:28.970 --> 43:30.570
- Batman.

43:30.570 --> 43:33.170
Robin's lame.

43:33.170 --> 43:34.810
- I just don't know that
people are gonna wanna watch

43:34.810 --> 43:36.690
a movie about a rich, good-looking guy

43:36.690 --> 43:39.210
literally getting away with murder.

43:39.210 --> 43:41.540
- You wanna know what I think?

43:41.540 --> 43:43.590
I think you're jealous.

43:43.590 --> 43:45.390
You come in here thinking
you know everything

43:45.390 --> 43:47.170
about serial killers and murderers.

43:47.170 --> 43:48.080
But you know what?

43:49.030 --> 43:52.330
Captain true crime
didn't come up with shit!

43:52.330 --> 43:53.820
- Fuck you, Seth!

43:53.820 --> 43:54.810
- Fuck me!

43:54.810 --> 43:57.470
- Yeah. I'm sorry I
didn't get any great info

43:57.470 --> 43:59.710
from her coworkers she barely talked to.

43:59.710 --> 44:02.750
I didn't get all invasive with her family.

44:02.750 --> 44:05.180
You know, you're a
well-dressed, good-looking guy.

44:05.180 --> 44:07.010
Do you care if we go
rifle through your room

44:07.010 --> 44:08.294
and see what you're hanging on to?

44:08.294 --> 44:09.133
- You know what?
- Guys, guys, just calm down.

44:09.133 --> 44:11.210
- I stuck my neck out for you!

44:11.210 --> 44:12.820
- To who? Yourself?

44:12.820 --> 44:13.710
- Oh, please!

44:13.710 --> 44:15.370
Look, I've seen your book numbers.

44:15.370 --> 44:17.483
You need this just as bad as I do.

44:18.370 --> 44:19.946
- This is bullshit.

44:19.946 --> 44:21.946
(sighs)

44:27.846 --> 44:30.714
(door slams)

44:30.714 --> 44:32.714
(sighs)

44:34.804 --> 44:37.417
- I'm gonna end up just like you.

44:37.417 --> 44:42.417
(emotional music)
(birds whistling)

45:08.466 --> 45:09.299
Hey.

45:10.286 --> 45:11.700
- Hey.

45:11.700 --> 45:12.617
- You okay?

45:14.404 --> 45:15.821
- Yeah, I'm okay.

45:23.547 --> 45:24.533
What's that?

45:26.130 --> 45:27.430
- Indirect peace offering?

45:34.360 --> 45:35.193
- Well, I wouldn't have said no

45:35.193 --> 45:38.510
to something stronger
than water, but thanks.

45:38.510 --> 45:39.343
- Yeah.

45:41.320 --> 45:43.720
Stuff got pretty heated in there.

45:43.720 --> 45:45.050
- I know. I'm...

45:46.727 --> 45:48.250
I'm sorry about the whole tantrum.

45:48.250 --> 45:52.893
He just seems to have a unique
ability to push my buttons.

45:55.280 --> 45:56.900
- Do you guys have a...

45:56.900 --> 45:57.770
Like a past?

45:57.770 --> 45:59.390
Maybe you dated?

45:59.390 --> 46:00.660
- No!

46:00.660 --> 46:01.850
No, we just...

46:02.790 --> 46:05.973
fundamentally disagree about
how to tell this story.

46:07.140 --> 46:08.400
- Right.

46:08.400 --> 46:10.200
- I mean, I knew there would
be creative differences,

46:10.200 --> 46:12.093
but not like this.

46:13.994 --> 46:15.680
I was already iffy about...

46:16.810 --> 46:20.030
bringing fame and notoriety
to this person anyway.

46:20.030 --> 46:22.520
And now we're talking about glamorizing

46:22.520 --> 46:24.033
what this sicko's doing?

46:26.240 --> 46:27.880
- Well...

46:27.880 --> 46:31.070
I mean, before you said it
was really interesting, right?

46:31.070 --> 46:32.540
- Yeah, it's interesting.

46:32.540 --> 46:35.883
But that doesn't make
it good or sympathetic.

46:40.340 --> 46:41.173
- Yeah.

46:42.210 --> 46:45.420
- I just think it could
be really harmful to...

46:46.260 --> 46:51.130
portray this killer as a hot, cool guy.

46:51.130 --> 46:52.860
I know that they think

46:52.860 --> 46:55.570
that they're doing something important

46:55.570 --> 46:58.621
or maybe even artistic with
this, but they're not there.

46:58.621 --> 47:00.650
They're just killing people.

47:00.650 --> 47:03.760
- What about the whole
gray area in writing,

47:03.760 --> 47:07.410
where characters aren't all
good or all bad, you know?

47:07.410 --> 47:09.940
- Right, but there is still
good and there is still bad.

47:09.940 --> 47:13.990
And I think the good are
the people that were killed.

47:13.990 --> 47:15.550
You know, they should
be living their lives

47:15.550 --> 47:17.580
but that chance was taken away from them

47:17.580 --> 47:20.913
by this person for their
own twisted reasons.

47:20.913 --> 47:22.490
(tense music)
It's not cool.

47:22.490 --> 47:23.360
It's not glamorous.

47:23.360 --> 47:25.230
It's sick. It's obsessive.

47:25.230 --> 47:26.581
They are a murderer!

47:26.581 --> 47:27.414
(cup crunches)
(water splashing)

47:27.414 --> 47:28.730
Shit!

47:28.730 --> 47:30.780
Are you okay?
- I'm so sorry!

47:30.780 --> 47:31.840
Shit!

47:31.840 --> 47:33.420
Yeah, yeah.

47:33.420 --> 47:34.900
- You are soaked!

47:34.900 --> 47:35.733
- I'm sorry.

47:35.733 --> 47:38.130
- Should we just call it for the day?

47:38.130 --> 47:39.090
Do you need to go home?

47:39.090 --> 47:40.250
- No. I...

47:41.750 --> 47:45.650
In my line of work, you need
to keep extra clothes on hand,

47:45.650 --> 47:47.040
so I can change.

47:47.040 --> 47:48.030
It's fine.

47:48.030 --> 47:48.863
- Okay.

47:51.270 --> 47:52.103
Go for it.

47:52.103 --> 47:52.936
- Sorry.

47:52.936 --> 47:55.250
- Yeah, I'll just take
a minute to cool down,

47:55.250 --> 47:56.600
and then we can go back in.

47:59.460 --> 48:01.504
Promise not to peak!

48:01.504 --> 48:04.337
(emotional music)

48:26.235 --> 48:28.235
(sighs)

48:38.540 --> 48:39.373
You ready?

48:41.320 --> 48:42.153
- Yeah.

48:44.296 --> 48:47.046
(car door shuts)

48:50.109 --> 48:52.109
(sighs)

48:53.386 --> 48:55.803
(door opens)

49:11.170 --> 49:12.003
- So...

49:12.920 --> 49:14.433
I regret some things.

49:16.170 --> 49:18.883
I'm sorry about what I
said. I was way out of line.

49:20.320 --> 49:24.683
To be completely honest, it's
not even really accurate.

49:26.100 --> 49:28.713
I actually did research your book sales.

49:30.960 --> 49:31.863
Pretty damn good.

49:33.000 --> 49:34.800
Better than anything I've ever done.

49:37.720 --> 49:38.553
Mark...

49:40.320 --> 49:43.500
did you know that we are
currently working with a member

49:43.500 --> 49:48.500
of John Anderson's top 200
true crime authors of 2020?

49:49.270 --> 49:50.750
- Yeah.

49:50.750 --> 49:52.940
- Did you already know that about me,

49:52.940 --> 49:55.600
or did you look it up when
I was outside just now?

49:55.600 --> 49:56.930
- Does that really matter a little yet?

49:56.930 --> 49:58.243
- A little, yes!

49:58.243 --> 49:59.160
- Whatever.

50:00.110 --> 50:01.693
- So where has this Seth been?

50:02.680 --> 50:04.007
- Under a lot of stress.

50:04.007 --> 50:04.840
(soft music)

50:04.840 --> 50:07.670
- Well, I like him. He's very charming.

50:07.670 --> 50:10.493
Well, I like him. He's
very charming, charming.

50:10.493 --> 50:13.410
(disturbing music)

50:57.860 --> 51:00.313
I need to be receptive to
ideas that aren't mine.

51:02.350 --> 51:03.520
I'm sorry.

51:03.520 --> 51:05.560
And it was really fucked up

51:05.560 --> 51:07.080
to imply that you were a murderer.

51:07.080 --> 51:08.760
I don't even know where that came from.

51:08.760 --> 51:11.760
- I mean, I do kind of look the part.

51:11.760 --> 51:13.970
- Well, you do dress really well.

51:13.970 --> 51:15.270
Okay.

51:15.270 --> 51:18.393
So, tell me about your
charming, magnetic killer.

51:19.770 --> 51:21.463
- How about I show you?

51:22.650 --> 51:23.990
- An act out?

51:23.990 --> 51:24.823
- Act out!

51:27.270 --> 51:29.920
I've been thinking about
this one for a little while.

51:31.418 --> 51:32.523
This here.

51:34.460 --> 51:36.130
Just a second.

51:36.130 --> 51:37.013
Just a second.

51:40.440 --> 51:41.500
Holly?

51:41.500 --> 51:44.290
- No! Why do I always
have to be the victim?

51:44.290 --> 51:46.500
- Do you really need to ask that?

51:46.500 --> 51:48.470
Holly? Flower names?

51:48.470 --> 51:50.220
Serial killer?

51:50.220 --> 51:52.010
- Holly is not a flower. It's a plant.

51:52.010 --> 51:53.073
- Close enough.

51:54.330 --> 51:55.600
- Mark!

51:55.600 --> 51:56.850
You haven't done one yet.

51:57.860 --> 51:59.420
Grab a seat.

51:59.420 --> 52:01.230
- I'm good, thanks. No.

52:01.230 --> 52:02.110
- Come on, man.

52:02.110 --> 52:04.700
- Be a team player! We're on a team now.

52:04.700 --> 52:05.533
- Go team!

52:07.003 --> 52:09.003
(sighs)

52:14.780 --> 52:15.920
Okay.

52:15.920 --> 52:17.219
All right.

52:17.219 --> 52:21.530
In this scenario, our killer
has our victim in a chair,

52:21.530 --> 52:23.173
hands tied behind their back.

52:25.304 --> 52:26.254
Behind on the back.

52:27.260 --> 52:28.138
Come on.

52:28.138 --> 52:29.300
(soft music)

52:29.300 --> 52:30.133
All right.

52:31.470 --> 52:35.553
So at this point, our victim is terrified.

52:36.670 --> 52:37.503
Alone.

52:38.850 --> 52:40.650
She doesn't know what's coming next.

52:43.070 --> 52:45.130
Is he making an advance?

52:45.130 --> 52:46.690
- Okay! Can we stop?

52:46.690 --> 52:48.650
Is that really necessary?

52:48.650 --> 52:50.523
- Your hands are supposed to be tied up.

52:51.524 --> 52:53.174
- Come on, man. Behind your back.

52:55.150 --> 52:55.983
- Okay.

52:57.740 --> 52:58.940
- All right.

52:58.940 --> 52:59.960
As I was saying...

53:01.890 --> 53:03.820
is he making an advance...

53:04.820 --> 53:05.960
or...

53:05.960 --> 53:07.694
is he just gonna blow
his fucking brains out?

53:07.694 --> 53:09.675
- Whoa!
- What the fuck?

53:09.675 --> 53:11.170
Is this real?

53:11.170 --> 53:12.380
- Why would I have a fake gun?

53:12.380 --> 53:13.430
- [Holly] Is it loaded?

53:13.430 --> 53:14.970
- No, it's not loaded!

53:14.970 --> 53:16.500
- What do you even have that?

53:16.500 --> 53:19.480
- Um, there's a murderer on the loose.

53:19.480 --> 53:23.380
- Don't point guns at
your friends, you weirdo!

53:23.380 --> 53:26.260
- You're right, you're right. I'm sorry.

53:26.260 --> 53:29.180
But did you see the look on his face?

53:29.180 --> 53:31.640
He didn't know what was gonna happen next!

53:31.640 --> 53:33.390
- You were pretty scared.

53:33.390 --> 53:35.290
- Yeah, there was a gun.

53:35.290 --> 53:36.763
- Damn near pissed his pants.

53:38.650 --> 53:40.600
- Are we done? Is that it?

53:40.600 --> 53:42.300
- So how are you feeling about it?

53:43.210 --> 53:45.530
I feel like you watched a lot of movies

53:45.530 --> 53:46.710
over the last 20 years,

53:46.710 --> 53:48.940
you regurgitated them into this cliche,

53:48.940 --> 53:49.970
and we just did that.

53:49.970 --> 53:53.491
It's like an animal with no
brain trying to create art.

53:53.491 --> 53:54.324
- Okay.

53:54.324 --> 53:55.980
- Wow.

53:55.980 --> 53:59.010
Well, you know, you're a big guy

53:59.010 --> 54:01.410
sitting in his friend's living room.

54:01.410 --> 54:03.440
You've got to put yourself
in the state of mind

54:03.440 --> 54:05.260
of one of these victims.

54:05.260 --> 54:08.740
You are a bright, accomplished young woman

54:08.740 --> 54:11.090
with people who love her.

54:11.090 --> 54:12.790
You should have your
whole life ahead of you,

54:12.790 --> 54:15.610
but you put your trust
in the wrong person,

54:15.610 --> 54:20.610
and now your whole life is
in the hands of this monster.

54:20.810 --> 54:21.760
- Damn you're good.

54:25.670 --> 54:26.830
- Okay.

54:26.830 --> 54:28.110
Sure.

54:28.110 --> 54:29.610
- So...

54:29.610 --> 54:30.443
try again.

54:30.443 --> 54:31.950
Think like that.

54:31.950 --> 54:32.800
- All right then.

54:33.830 --> 54:34.980
Hands behind your back.

54:38.220 --> 54:39.660
As I was saying...

54:41.750 --> 54:46.750
he's had this victim for
weeks, living off scraps.

54:47.190 --> 54:49.933
She's hungry, weak.

54:51.430 --> 54:53.813
Not knowing what's coming next.

54:54.760 --> 54:59.500
Her dreams, her aspirations
all fading away...

54:59.500 --> 55:02.140
all with just a tight squeeze.

55:02.140 --> 55:04.630
- Stop, stop, stop! Okay?

55:04.630 --> 55:08.980
Take a fucking second and
do something that matters!

55:08.980 --> 55:11.320
You're not accomplishing anything!

55:11.320 --> 55:12.780
What are you doing? Are
you gonna be in the movie?

55:12.780 --> 55:15.460
Why are we doing this? Are you acting?

55:15.460 --> 55:17.280
We're just spinning our tires!

55:17.280 --> 55:18.780
How many times have we met up?

55:19.650 --> 55:22.070
I'm gonna take a second
and leave and do something

55:22.070 --> 55:24.770
to actually help us push
this story forward, you know,

55:24.770 --> 55:25.603
figure something out.

55:25.603 --> 55:26.630
If you guys wanna do the same,

55:26.630 --> 55:29.110
maybe you should do that and
we can get something done.

55:29.110 --> 55:30.110
Okay?

55:30.110 --> 55:32.253
I'm sorry. I just, I gotta go.

55:36.882 --> 55:38.890
- Was it something I said?

55:38.890 --> 55:40.423
- You pointed a gun at him!

55:41.620 --> 55:42.453
- Too much?

55:46.424 --> 55:48.924
(eerie music)

56:02.887 --> 56:05.887
(crickets chirping)

56:07.217 --> 56:10.050
(startling music)

56:31.295 --> 56:33.050
- Oh! (laughs)

56:33.050 --> 56:33.960
You must be Mark.

56:33.960 --> 56:34.970
- Yeah. Daisy?

56:34.970 --> 56:36.780
- Yeah, it's nice to meet you!

56:36.780 --> 56:38.400
- Yeah, you too.

56:38.400 --> 56:39.233
You...

56:39.233 --> 56:40.553
- Yeah, you wanna sit down?

56:41.450 --> 56:44.560
- So, this is a nice park.

56:44.560 --> 56:47.143
- It's really nice. It's
been a beautiful day.

56:48.150 --> 56:50.917
- You would think. You would think.

56:50.917 --> 56:53.060
- Did you have a rough day?

56:53.060 --> 56:56.370
- Yeah, work stuff. It was kinda bad.

56:56.370 --> 56:57.203
- I hear ya.

56:57.203 --> 56:58.484
Yeah, work. Ugh.

56:58.484 --> 56:59.317
(laughs)

56:59.317 --> 57:00.850
- What do you do?

57:00.850 --> 57:04.290
- I am an art teacher
for middle schoolers.

57:04.290 --> 57:05.123
- Wow!

57:05.123 --> 57:05.970
- Mm-hm.

57:05.970 --> 57:06.960
- That must be...

57:08.220 --> 57:09.053
unbearable.

57:11.230 --> 57:12.170
- Um...

57:13.679 --> 57:14.910
not really.

57:14.910 --> 57:17.950
I mean, I love to teach
art, and I love kids,

57:17.950 --> 57:19.530
so it's been...

57:19.530 --> 57:20.500
It's pretty fulfilling.

57:20.500 --> 57:23.770
It can have its challenges
though. Definitely.

57:23.770 --> 57:26.670
- I'm actually pretty
creative myself, I guess.

57:26.670 --> 57:27.797
I'm a photographer.

57:27.797 --> 57:28.630
- Oh!

57:28.630 --> 57:30.490
- And I work on some film
projects here and there,

57:30.490 --> 57:32.014
getting into that.

57:32.014 --> 57:34.600
- Wow! That sounds like fun.

57:34.600 --> 57:35.870
- Well, sometimes.

57:35.870 --> 57:38.790
I actually had a meeting
today that kind of went crazy,

57:38.790 --> 57:40.490
like I was saying.

57:40.490 --> 57:43.320
They won't really listen to
me and take my input on stuff.

57:43.320 --> 57:45.980
And it's actually a topic
that I know all about

57:45.980 --> 57:47.440
and they won't even recognize that

57:47.440 --> 57:49.220
and listen to what I have to say.

57:49.220 --> 57:50.810
And it gets really frustrating,

57:50.810 --> 57:53.010
and I'm not really sure
what to do about it.

57:54.880 --> 57:55.713
I don't know.

57:55.713 --> 57:56.800
I'm rambling though. Sorry.

57:56.800 --> 58:00.060
- Well, I mean, it's hard
when you're not heard.

58:00.060 --> 58:01.190
I can understand that.

58:01.190 --> 58:02.410
And don't worry about the rambling.

58:02.410 --> 58:04.380
I'm pretty nervous myself.

58:04.380 --> 58:05.683
This is my first time.

